*libXfont-1.3.0 (06 Jul 2007)

  06 Jul 2007; Donnie Berkholz <dberkholz@gentoo.org>;
  +libXfont-1.3.0.ebuild:
  Bump. Adds a feature that might be useful for our font packages of using
  symlinks to point at font directories to avoid configuration changes in
  xorg.conf or xfs config. Also has some dead code cleanup, etc.

  24 Jun 2007; Joshua Kinard <kumba@gentoo.org> libXfont-1.2.8.ebuild:
  Stable on mips, per #175465.

  21 Apr 2007; Joshua Baergen <joshuabaergen@gentoo.org>
  -libXfont-1.2.6.ebuild, -libXfont-1.2.7.ebuild:
  Drop unused versions.

  17 Apr 2007; Jose Luis Rivero <yoswink@gentoo.org>
  libXfont-1.2.7-r1.ebuild:
  Stable on alpha wrt bug #172575

  12 Apr 2007; Jeroen Roovers <jer@gentoo.org> libXfont-1.2.7-r1.ebuild:
  Stable for HPPA (bug #172575).

  11 Apr 2007; Tobias Scherbaum <dertobi123@gentoo.org>
  libXfont-1.2.7-r1.ebuild:
  ppc stable, bug #172575

  11 Apr 2007; Markus Rothe <corsair@gentoo.org> libXfont-1.2.7-r1.ebuild:
  Stable on ppc64; bug #172575

  11 Apr 2007; Peter Weller <welp@gentoo.org> libXfont-1.2.7-r1.ebuild:
  Stable on amd64 wrt bug 172575

  11 Apr 2007; Raúl Porcel <armin76@gentoo.org> libXfont-1.2.7-r1.ebuild:
  ia64 + x86 stable wrt security bug 172575

  11 Apr 2007; Ferris McCormick <fmccor@gentoo.org>
  libXfont-1.2.7-r1.ebuild:
  Stable on sparc --- Security Bug #172575 --- the required xorg-server version
  is already stable.

*libXfont-1.2.8 (05 Apr 2007)

  05 Apr 2007; Donnie Berkholz <dberkholz@gentoo.org>;
  +libXfont-1.2.8.ebuild:
  Bump. Includes the security patch as well as a fix to use loadable font
  modules and other irrelevant stuff.

  05 Apr 2007; Donnie Berkholz <dberkholz@gentoo.org>;
  libXfont-1.2.2-r1.ebuild:
  Fix keywords.

*libXfont-1.2.7-r1 (05 Apr 2007)
*libXfont-1.2.2-r1 (05 Apr 2007)

  05 Apr 2007; Donnie Berkholz <dberkholz@gentoo.org>;
  +files/xorg-libXfont-1.2.7-bdf-fontdir.diff, +libXfont-1.2.2-r1.ebuild,
  +libXfont-1.2.7-r1.ebuild:
  (#172575) Security bump. CVE 2007-1351: bdf font parsing integer overflow
  and CVE 2007-1352: fonts.dir file parsing integer overflow.

  28 Jan 2007; Donnie Berkholz <dberkholz@gentoo.org>;
  -files/1.2.0-pcfread-git.diff, -libXfont-1.1.0-r1.ebuild,
  -libXfont-1.2.0.ebuild, -libXfont-1.2.0-r1.ebuild,
  -libXfont-1.2.0-r2.ebuild:
  (#164196) Clean out vulnerable ebuilds.

  28 Jan 2007; Alexander H. Færøy <eroyf@gentoo.org>
  libXfont-1.2.2.ebuild:
  Stable on MIPS; bug #164196

*libXfont-1.2.7 (24 Jan 2007)

  24 Jan 2007; Donnie Berkholz <dberkholz@gentoo.org>;
  +libXfont-1.2.7.ebuild:
  Bump. Now accepts empty font paths, and fixes a crasher when trying to scale
  a built-in bitmap font.

*libXfont-1.2.6 (16 Dec 2006)

  16 Dec 2006; Joshua Baergen <joshuabaergen@gentoo.org>
  -libXfont-1.2.5.ebuild, +libXfont-1.2.6.ebuild:
  Version bump for 7.2.  Build/dist fix, and enable type1 support by default.
  Closes #157710.

*libXfont-1.2.5 (02 Dec 2006)

  02 Dec 2006; Joshua Baergen <joshuabaergen@gentoo.org>
  -libXfont-1.2.4.ebuild, +libXfont-1.2.5.ebuild:
  1.2.4 had build problems on some systems - replace with 1.2.5.

*libXfont-1.2.4 (02 Dec 2006)

  02 Dec 2006; Joshua Baergen <joshuabaergen@gentoo.org>
